3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Gate.io calculates RUNE/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a premium index formula. The funding payment occurs between long and short position holders based on the 8-hour time-weighted average premium. Gate.io caps funding rates at ±0.375% per interval to prevent extreme payments during volatile THORChain ecosystem events. Positions held at funding time automatically settle the payment without affecting margin requirements."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","RUNE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE funding rates often diverge from major cryptocurrencies due to its specific use case in cross-chain liquidity provision and yield farming cycles. The token's volatility around THORChain network upgrades and liquidity pool incentive changes creates funding rate inefficiencies. Gate.io's broad DeFi token coverage makes it easier to hedge RUNE positions against correlated assets in the same ecosystem."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical RUNE Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE/USDT funding rates on Gate.io have shown distinct patterns tied to THORChain's operational cycles and cross-chain DeFi trends. During network upgrade periods, funding rates often swing negative as traders short RUNE ahead of potential technical issues, creating opportunities for contrarian positions. The token typically experiences positive funding during DeFi summer periods when cross-chain yield farming drives demand. Gate.io's 8-hour intervals help smooth out short-term volatility compared to exchanges with more frequent funding updates. Historical data shows funding rates ranging from -0.3% to +0.2% during major THORChain ecosystem events."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Market Dynamics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE's mid-tier trading volume creates regular funding rate arbitrage opportunities, especially during periods of high DeFi activity or network uncertainty. Gate.io's competitive 0.015% maker fees allow profitable arbitrage even with smaller funding rate differentials compared to higher-fee exchanges. The exchange's extensive altcoin coverage enables delta-neutral strategies using correlated DeFi tokens as hedges. Funding rate convergence typically occurs within 2-3 intervals as arbitrageurs exploit significant deviations. Best opportunities often arise during Asian trading hours when THORChain community activity peaks."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Position Management"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE's exposure to smart contract risks and cross-chain bridge vulnerabilities can cause sudden price gaps that affect funding rate calculations. Gate.io's position limits may restrict large arbitrage trades during high volatility periods, requiring position scaling strategies. The token's correlation with Bitcoin during market stress can reduce the effectiveness of crypto-neutral arbitrage approaches. Traders should monitor THORChain governance proposals and network capacity metrics that can trigger unexpected funding rate movements. Gate.io's Ethereum-only deposit limitations for some regions may create timing constraints for position adjustments during critical funding windows."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Gate.io update RUNE/USDT funding rates?","answer":"Gate.io updates RUNE/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The funding payment is automatically settled between long and short positions based on the calculated rate."},{"question":"What are typical RUNE funding rate ranges on Gate.io?","answer":"RUNE funding rates on Gate.io typically range from -0.1% to +0.15% per 8-hour period during normal market conditions. During major THORChain events or DeFi cycles, rates can reach the ±0.375% cap limits."},{"question":"Can I hedge RUNE positions with other DeFi tokens on Gate.io?","answer":"Yes, Gate.io's extensive DeFi token coverage allows hedging RUNE positions with correlated assets like SUSHI, UNI, or CAKE. This helps create delta-neutral strategies while capturing funding rate differentials."},{"question":"How do THORChain network events affect RUNE funding rates?","answer":"THORChain network upgrades, liquidity pool changes, and cross-chain bridge updates often create funding rate volatility. Traders typically short RUNE before uncertain events, pushing funding rates negative and creating arbitrage opportunities."}]}]
